## 10. First Things Every Developer Must Learn

1. `organization_id` is the owner of business data
2. modules are not features
3. providers are not product concepts
4. `results` is the module name, `research_results` is the workflow table
5. canonical entity/analysis tables are the final source of truth
6. RLS is mandatory
7. `feature-system/` owns capability availability
8. services must be used instead of scattered page-level queries

---

## 11. Most Common Mistakes

Do not:
- create new top-level modules casually
- turn shortlist or dossiers into top-level navigation
- hardcode sidebar tabs
- hardcode role checks throughout components
- build final pages from legacy result blobs
- put Supabase queries directly in page components
- use provider names as feature names
- let local UI state become the source of truth for workflow state

